        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 23 at 1:31PM PDT by NWS Hanford CA</headline>
        <description>At 131 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 20
miles south of Mammoth Lakes, moving northwest at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lake Thomas Edison, Mount Tom, High Sierra, Florence Lake, Graveyard
Meadow, Kaiser Point, Upper Burnt Corral, and Volcanic Knob.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
